*kyaamt kaa chottaa saa mNzr!*

ek shaagird ne apne ustaad se puuchaa:
ustaad jii! yh aakhirt meN hisaab kitaab kaise hogaa?
ustaad ne thodd'ii der socaa phir apnii jgh se utthe aur saare shaagirdoN meN kuch paise baaNtte, unhoNne phle ldd'ke ko 100 dirhm duusre ko 75 tiisre ko 60 cauthe ko 50 paaNcve ko 25 chtthe ko 10 aur saatveN ko 5 aur jis ldd'ke ne svaal puuchaa thaa usse fkt ek dirhm diyaa / 

ldddhkaa ustaad kii is tqsiim pr bhut gmgiin aur dukhii thaa, use apnii tauhiin mhsuus ho rhii thii ki ustaad ne aakhir use sbse kmtr aur km musthiq kyoNkr jaanaa...??

ustaad ne muskuraate hue sbko dekhte hue khaa: sb ldddhkoN ko chuttttii, tum sb log jaa kr in paisoN ko puuraa puuraa khrc kro, ab hmaarii mulaakaat hphte vaale din bstii ke naanbaaii ke tNduur pr hogii / 

hphte vaale din saare sttuuddeNtts naanbaaii ke tNduur pr phuNc ge, jhaaN ustaad phle se hii maujuud sbkaa iNtzaar kr rhe the / 
sb ldddhkoN ke aa jaane ke baad ustaad ne unheN btaayaa ki tum meN se hr ek is tNduur pr crh kr mujhe apne apne paisoN ko khaaN khrc kiyaa hai... kaa hisaab degaa / 

phle vaale ldddhke, jise ek sau dirhm mile the, ko dhkte tNduur kii muNdder pr crhaa kr ustaad ne puuchaa: btaao, mere die hue sau dirhm kaise khrc kie the..?

jlte tNduur se niklte sholoN kii tpish aur grm muNdder kii hraart se preshaan ldddhkaa ek pair rkhtaa aur duusraa utthaataa....
khrc kie hue paisoN ko yaad krtaa aur btaataa ki paaNc dirhm kii brphii lii thii,ds caay naashte meN, ds ke aNguur, paaNc dirhm kii rottiyaaN aur isii trh baakii ke khrce.................
ldd'ke ke pair grmii se jl rhe the to baakii kaa jism tNduur se niklte sholoN se jhuls rhaa thaa, httaa ke itnii sii der meN use pyaas bhii lg gii thii, aur alphaaj bhii ldd'khdd'aanaa shuruu /   mushkil se hisaab dekr niice utraa, uske baad duusraa ldd'kaa phir tiisraa aur phir isii trh baakii ldd'ke.......
yhaaN tk ke us ldd'ke kii baarii aa phuNcii jise ek dirhm milaa thaa / 

ustaad ne use bhii khaa ke tum bhii tNduur pr cddh' jaao aur apnaa hisaab do /  ldd'kaa jldii se tNduur pr cddh'aa, bgair kisii tvkkuph ke bolaa ki maiNne ek dirhm kii ghr ke lie dhniyaa kii gddddii khriidii thii aur saath hii muskuraataa huaa niice utr kr ke saamne jaakr khdd'aa ho gyaa, jbki baakii ke ldd'ke abhii tk niddhaal baitthe apne pairoN pr paanii ddaalkr tthNddaa kr rhe the / 

ustaad ne sb ldd'koN ko mutvjjeh krke us ldd'ke ko khaastaur pr sunaate hue khaa : bcco! yh kyaamt vaale din ke hisaab kitaab kaa ek chotte se chottaa mNjr naamaa thaa, hr iNsaan se usko jis kdr ataa kiyaa gyaa ke braabr hisaab hogaa / 

ldd'ke ne ustaad ko mohbbt se dekhte hue khaa ki aapne jitnaa km mujhe diyaa us pr mujhe rshk aur aapkii ataa pr pyaar aa rhaa hai, taahm allaah tbaark v taalaa kii misaal to bhut aalaa aur uuNcii hai / 

allaah taalaa hmeN apne hisaab kii shiddt se bcaae aur hmaare saath maaphii aur drgujaar vaalaa maamlaa phrmaa kr bgair hisaab kitaab jnnt meN daakhil phrmaae /   aamiin

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
*Small scene of doom!*

A disciple asked his teacher:
Master! How will this be settled in the end?
The master thought for a while, then got up from his seat and distributed some money among all the disciples, he gave 100 dirhams to the second boy, 75 to the third, 60 to the fourth, 50 to the fifth, 25 to the sixth, 10 to the sixth and 5 to the seventh, and the boy who asked the question Gave him only one dirham.

The boy was very sad and sad on this division of Ustad, he was feeling insulted that why did Ustad consider him the lowest and the least worthy...??

The teacher smilingly looked at everyone and said: Holiday to all the boys, all of you go and spend this money completely, now we will meet on a weekday at the township's baker's tandoor.

On the weekday, all the students reached the baker's oven, where the teacher was already waiting for everyone present.
After all the boys had come, the teacher told them that each one of you would climb this tandoor and give me an account of where you have spent your money.

After putting the first boy, who had received one hundred dirhams, on the hood of the burning oven, the master asked: Tell me, how did you spend the hundred dirhams given by me..?

Troubled by the heat of the flames coming out of the burning oven and the heat of the hot munder, the boy kept one leg and raised the other....
Remembers the money spent and tells that he had taken ice cream for five dirhams, ten tea for breakfast, ten grapes, five dirham breads and so on for the rest of the expenses. ...
The boy's feet were burning with heat, while the rest of the body was burning with the flames coming out of the oven, he was thirsty in such a short time, and the words also started faltering. He got down after giving the account with difficulty, after that the second boy then the third and then the rest of the boys like this......
Even the turn of the boy who had got one dirham came.

Ustad also told him that you also climb the oven and give your account. The boy quickly climbed the oven, said without hesitation that he had bought a bunch of coriander for the house for one dirham, and at the same time, smiling, got down and stood in front of the oven, while the rest of the boys were still sitting motionless on their feet. But they were cooling it by pouring water on it.

The master, after explaining to all the boys, specially telling that boy, said: Children! This was a small scene of the Book, according to the Day of Judgment, every person will be accounted for according to the amount he was given.

The boy looked at the teacher with love and said that I am jealous of the little you have given me and I love your gift, but the example of Allah Tabarak and Taala is very high and high.

May Allah Ta'ala save us from the intensity of his calculations and make us enter Jannah without accounting by saying a matter of forgiveness and forgiveness with us. Amen

In Ramadan Juhar Time 1.45 P. M.
